AWARD-WINNING gospel artist Takie Ndou has presented his driver Khumbudzo Mbedzi with a brand new car. He took to his social media and explained that Khumbudzo is the reason he’s always on time at gigs. His post reads as follows: “This guy has been a big blessing and faithful to my ministry for the past seven years and he is the one who makes sure I arrive at all my gigs on time. I thank God that I can be able to appreciate him like this, although I wish I could do more but am sure God has more blessings for you in 2022 bro. Keep serving and being faithful to God @khumbudzo. Congratulations Bro.” Khumbudzo couldn’t be happier for the gift. He responded to Takie and wrote: “Thank you so much Mkomana, Thank you.” Takie’s post was accompanied by a photo of himself giving Khumbudzo the car keys. ALSO READ : OLIVER MTUKUDZI SINGS FROM THE GRAVE! His friends, fans and colleagues in the gospel fraternity including Benjamin Dube, Omega Khunou and Putuma Tiso congratulated Khumbudzo and praised Takkie for his gesture. Mieta Ntombosindiso Sishuba commented: “Wow. You are one of a kind in God’s Kingdom Takie. May the Lord be with you throughout your journey. God bless his heart even more.” Daniel Ralesego said: “What Sir did is beyond the gift. God has seen your heart. Prepare yourself for the next wave of glory is your ministry, Sir. Thank you and thank you. More glorious years ahead.” Mpho Munyai wrote: “Appreciation is very important. May God increase your territory in Jesus’ name. Continue to serve, my brother.” 